1
00:02:26,847 --> 00:02:29,680
Quiet, Mirza. Mirza, quiet now.

2
00:02:31,047 --> 00:02:34,835
- Good afternoon, madame.
- Yes, what is it?

3
00:02:35,007 --> 00:02:38,602
I'm sorry to bother you.
I was told about an apartment.

4
00:02:43,047 --> 00:02:45,481
This is the right building, isn't it?

5
00:02:45,647 --> 00:02:47,399
Who told you?

6
00:02:47,567 --> 00:02:52,118
A friend of mine.
Well, a relation, actually.

7
00:02:52,287 --> 00:02:54,323
The door.

8
00:02:55,087 --> 00:02:57,840
I gather it's a small
two-room apartment?

9
00:02:58,007 --> 00:03:02,444
Think that's all I got to do? Some
people think a concierge is a slave.

10
00:03:02,607 --> 00:03:07,044
Not me. Would it be more convenient
if I came back later?

11
00:03:07,207 --> 00:03:12,361
You have to speak with Monsieur Zy.
I can only show the apartment.

12
00:03:12,527 --> 00:03:16,600
I don't want to be a nuisance,
but if it were at all possible,

13
00:03:16,767 --> 00:03:21,887
and if I might offer you some
small compensation for your trouble,

14
00:03:22,047 --> 00:03:24,436
which is only reasonable.

15
00:03:28,447 --> 00:03:33,601
What a lovely little dog you... you are.
You're Mirza, aren't you?

16
00:03:34,207 --> 00:03:38,280
It's... It's a nice name, Mirza.

17
00:03:50,247 --> 00:03:51,965
I'm sorry.

18
00:05:07,167 --> 00:05:10,842
The previous tenant threw herself
out of the window.

19
00:05:12,967 --> 00:05:15,561
You can still see where she fell.

20
00:05:16,807 --> 00:05:18,399
Look.

21
00:05:23,007 --> 00:05:25,726
He's going to have to fix that.

22
00:05:27,207 --> 00:05:31,200
She's not dead yet,
though she might as well be.

23
00:05:31,367 --> 00:05:34,325
She's in the Bretonneau Hospital.

24
00:05:34,487 --> 00:05:36,876
What if she gets better?

25
00:05:37,047 --> 00:05:41,882
Don't worry. She won't get better.
You're on to a good thing here.

26
00:05:42,047 --> 00:05:45,039
Poor woman. What are the terms?

27
00:05:45,207 --> 00:05:48,483
There's a fee for water.
The plumbing is new.

28
00:05:48,647 --> 00:05:50,638
The tap was on the landing.

29
00:05:50,807 --> 00:05:55,881
- And the toilet?
- Over there. Go around the corridor.

30
00:05:56,047 --> 00:05:58,845
That's a view worth looking at!

31
00:06:04,127 --> 00:06:06,197
How much is the premium?

32
00:06:06,367 --> 00:06:08,961
The rent is 600 francs a month.

33
00:06:09,127 --> 00:06:14,884
The premium I'm not sure about.
I think he wants 5,000 francs.

34
00:06:15,047 --> 00:06:18,483
5,000? That's a lot of money.

35
00:06:18,647 --> 00:06:23,960
It's not my business. You'll have to talk
to Monsieur Zy. He lives down here.

36
00:06:26,167 --> 00:06:28,635
I have to get back now.

37
00:06:58,807 --> 00:07:01,275
<i>All right, we're not deaf.</i>

38
00:07:02,887 --> 00:07:06,357
- We don't give to charity.
- It's about the apartment.

39
00:07:06,527 --> 00:07:09,724
- What apartment?
- On the floor above.

40
00:07:09,887 --> 00:07:12,447
Could I speak to Monsieur Zy?

41
00:07:41,087 --> 00:07:42,759
Good afternoon.

42
00:07:53,607 --> 00:07:58,727
- Have you seen the apartment?
- Yes. I wanted to discuss the terms.

43
00:08:00,887 --> 00:08:03,640
5,000 premium, 600 a month.

44
00:08:03,807 --> 00:08:08,437
That's a lot of money.
I couldn't pay more than 4,000.

45
00:08:12,327 --> 00:08:16,605
- The concierge told you about the water.
- Yes, she did.

46
00:08:16,767 --> 00:08:19,520
It's damned hard to find an apartment.

47
00:08:19,687 --> 00:08:24,442
A student on the sixth floor gave me
half that for a single room.

48
00:08:24,607 --> 00:08:28,202
Don't get me wrong.
I'm not criticising your apartment,

49
00:08:28,367 --> 00:08:30,562
but the toilet is a problem.

50
00:08:30,727 --> 00:08:34,686
Suppose I got sick, which I don't
often do, I can assure you,

51
00:08:34,847 --> 00:08:40,479
and I had to relieve myself in the night.
It wouldn't be very convenient.

52
00:08:40,647 --> 00:08:45,402
On the other hand, I could pay you
the 4,000 right away in cash.

53
00:08:45,567 --> 00:08:50,277
It's not only a question of money,
let's be clear about that, monsieur...

54
00:08:50,447 --> 00:08:52,438
Trelkovsky.

55
00:08:52,607 --> 00:08:54,518
Trelkovsky.

56
00:08:54,687 --> 00:08:57,884
I won't exactly starve
without your 5,000.

57
00:08:58,047 --> 00:09:02,802
I'm renting the apartment because it's
vacant. They don't grow on trees.

58
00:09:02,967 --> 00:09:07,165
Of course. It's perfectly reasonable.
I understand your point.

59
00:09:07,327 --> 00:09:09,557
Could I offer you a cigarette?

60
00:09:09,727 --> 00:09:15,438
You want 5,000, fine. But if you got paid
by cheque, you'd have to declare it.

61
00:09:15,607 --> 00:09:18,804
Wouldn't you rather get 4,000 in cash?

62
00:09:18,967 --> 00:09:22,164
I'd rather get 5,000 in cash.

63
00:09:24,487 --> 00:09:29,800
It's perfectly natural. Anyway,
the former tenant is not dead yet.

64
00:09:29,967 --> 00:09:34,006
If she comes back, you won't even
get 4,000. You get nothing.

65
00:09:34,167 --> 00:09:38,365
Are you married? Excuse the question,
but it's because of children.

66
00:09:38,527 --> 00:09:42,725
This is a very quiet building.
My wife and I are getting on now.

67
00:09:42,887 --> 00:09:44,923
I wouldn't say that, Monsieur Zy.

68
00:09:45,087 --> 00:09:49,524
I know what I'm saying. My wife and I
are getting on. We don't like noise.

69
00:09:49,687 --> 00:09:53,202
You needn't worry.
I'm very quiet and I'm a bachelor.

70
00:09:54,687 --> 00:09:57,360
Bachelors can be a problem, too.

71
00:09:57,527 --> 00:10:00,519
If you want a place to entertain girls,

72
00:10:00,687 --> 00:10:03,918
I'd rather take 2,000 and give it
to someone more needy.

73
00:10:04,087 --> 00:10:06,442
I quite agree, but I'm not that type.

74
00:10:07,127 --> 00:10:12,520
I can't give you a definite answer while
Mademoiselle Choule is still alive.

75
00:10:12,687 --> 00:10:17,477
But I like you. You seem to be
a serious young man to me.

76
00:10:33,287 --> 00:10:36,120
I want to visit Mademoiselle Choule.

77
00:10:45,007 --> 00:10:46,599
Simone Choule?

78
00:10:46,767 --> 00:10:49,600
- Are you a relative?
- I'm a friend.

79
00:11:01,007 --> 00:11:03,237
Can I help you?

80
00:11:03,407 --> 00:11:05,602
- Are you the head nurse?
- Yes.

81
00:11:05,767 --> 00:11:11,205
Good. I was told at reception to see you
first. It's about Mademoiselle Choule.

82
00:11:11,367 --> 00:11:14,165
- Bed 18.
- May I see her?

83
00:11:14,327 --> 00:11:18,366
She's not to be disturbed.
She was in a coma until yesterday.

84
00:11:18,527 --> 00:11:21,678
Go ahead, but don't try to talk to her.

85
00:11:55,567 --> 00:11:58,286
He said he'd come by Wednesday...

86
00:11:58,447 --> 00:12:00,961
Are you a friend of hers?

87
00:12:01,727 --> 00:12:03,319
Excuse me.

88
00:12:09,447 --> 00:12:13,759
I can't believe it. I just can't believe it.

89
00:12:13,927 --> 00:12:18,921
I was with her the night before.
No, two nights before.

90
00:12:19,087 --> 00:12:21,601
She was in such good spirits.

91
00:12:23,127 --> 00:12:25,436
Why would she do a thing like that?

92
00:12:25,607 --> 00:12:29,885
To tell you the truth, I'm not close.
I hardly know her.

93
00:12:30,047 --> 00:12:34,279
But believe me, I'm terribly upset
about what's happened.

94
00:12:35,687 --> 00:12:37,484
It's awful.

95
00:12:38,727 --> 00:12:40,604
Simone?

96
00:12:41,047 --> 00:12:42,799
Simone?

97
00:12:43,127 --> 00:12:46,005
You do recognise me, don't you?

98
00:12:46,167 --> 00:12:47,964
It's me. Stella.

99
00:12:48,887 --> 00:12:53,756
Your friend Stella.
Don't you recognise me?

100
00:13:02,767 --> 00:13:04,917
You'll have to leave now.

101
00:13:05,087 --> 00:13:07,123
Your bag.

102
00:13:07,287 --> 00:13:09,437
Is there any hope of saving her?

103
00:13:09,607 --> 00:13:12,485
If we can save her, we save her.

104
00:13:36,447 --> 00:13:40,122
Careful.
You mustn't give in to your grief.

105
00:13:42,767 --> 00:13:48,922
If you like, we could have something
to drink. I think it would help you.

106
00:13:49,087 --> 00:13:51,203
There is a...

107
00:13:59,447 --> 00:14:00,926
Here.

108
00:14:10,887 --> 00:14:13,242
What would you like to drink?

109
00:14:14,727 --> 00:14:16,604
I don't know.

110
00:14:16,767 --> 00:14:19,884
I'll have a beer. No, a coffee.

111
00:14:20,047 --> 00:14:23,881
- Coffee. And the lady?
- I don't want a coffee.

112
00:14:24,047 --> 00:14:27,323
Have something strong.
It will pick you up.

113
00:14:27,487 --> 00:14:29,921
I'll have a small glass of Beaujolais.

114
00:14:30,087 --> 00:14:33,875
Small glass of Beaujolais
and... a martini.

115
00:14:34,047 --> 00:14:36,925
- No coffee?
- No, no. A martini.

116
00:14:41,367 --> 00:14:44,484
I forgot. I have a phone call to make.

117
00:14:44,647 --> 00:14:47,115
I'll be right back.

118
00:15:04,207 --> 00:15:07,483
- Come here.
- All right, I'm coming.

119
00:15:09,087 --> 00:15:11,647
I'll never understand suicide.

120
00:15:13,447 --> 00:15:18,475
I have no argument against it
but it's beyond my comprehension.

121
00:15:18,647 --> 00:15:21,161
Did you ever discuss it with her?

122
00:15:21,567 --> 00:15:23,159
Never.

123
00:15:24,407 --> 00:15:26,967
I just can't believe it.

124
00:15:28,287 --> 00:15:31,085
It's terrible. Terrible.

125
00:15:31,847 --> 00:15:33,280
It's terrible.

126
00:15:33,447 --> 00:15:37,759
Could it have been a disappointment
in love? Something like that?

127
00:15:37,927 --> 00:15:41,761
- Who with?
- I don't know. Some man.

128
00:15:41,927 --> 00:15:45,124
You know she wasn't interested in men.

129
00:15:45,287 --> 00:15:48,199
Yes, I know, but...

130
00:15:48,367 --> 00:15:52,280
Women as sensitive as she was,
she is, I mean,

131
00:15:52,447 --> 00:15:58,363
tend to have much more complicated
relationships than they seem to.

132
00:15:59,727 --> 00:16:02,605
Perhaps she will pull out of it anyway.

133
00:16:02,767 --> 00:16:04,962
I doubt it.

134
00:16:05,407 --> 00:16:09,195
Did you notice that she didn't
even recognise me?

135
00:16:11,247 --> 00:16:12,919
A tragedy.

136
00:16:17,167 --> 00:16:20,000
Hey, man. Got any bread for an artist?

137
00:16:23,647 --> 00:16:27,720
- I don't have any change.
- I don't care. I'll take what you got.

138
00:16:27,887 --> 00:16:29,684
I've only got notes.

139
00:16:29,847 --> 00:16:33,123
Don't look cheap
in front of your girlfriend.

140
00:16:34,087 --> 00:16:36,078
Not a word of thanks.

141
00:16:36,247 --> 00:16:41,037
I don't like tramps. You shouldn't
have given him anything.

142
00:18:16,167 --> 00:18:21,082
- Would you like to have a drink?
- No. Thanks.

143
00:18:21,247 --> 00:18:24,637
Right. Goodbye then.

144
00:18:24,807 --> 00:18:27,275
- Goodbye.
- Hope to see you soon.

145
00:18:44,967 --> 00:18:48,960
- What is it?
- Just came over from CNMA.

146
00:18:49,127 --> 00:18:51,846
- Was it sent by Monsieur Lott?
- Right.

147
00:18:52,007 --> 00:18:56,080
- That must be the Villa LeDuc.
- Yes, that's right.

148
00:18:56,247 --> 00:19:00,160
Yes, that's the Villa LeDuc.
"Unmounted number 2601.

149
00:19:00,327 --> 00:19:05,959
"Make a detailed copy of spire as
indicated in the lower left-hand corner."

150
00:19:06,127 --> 00:19:08,800
You have to do it by next Thursday.

151
00:19:42,967 --> 00:19:47,279
I'm calling to ask if you have
any news about Simone Choule.

152
00:19:47,447 --> 00:19:50,280
- <i>What department is she in?</i>
- Surgery?

153
00:19:50,447 --> 00:19:54,406
- <i>Choule? With a C?</i>
- That's right. Simone Choule.

154
00:19:54,567 --> 00:19:59,402
- <i>Are you a relative?</i>
- No. I'm a friend.

155
00:19:59,567 --> 00:20:02,877
<i>The patient died at 4.20 p.m. Yesterday.</i>

156
00:20:05,447 --> 00:20:07,165
Thank you.

157
00:20:08,327 --> 00:20:11,000
Yes... Goodbye.

158
00:24:21,967 --> 00:24:23,923
- Morning, monsieur.
- Morning.

159
00:24:24,087 --> 00:24:27,557
- Live opposite?
- Yes. I just moved in.

160
00:24:27,727 --> 00:24:32,278
You rented the apartment of that girl
that jumped out of the window?

161
00:24:32,447 --> 00:24:34,563
Yes. Did you know her?

162
00:24:34,727 --> 00:24:36,957
Sure I did. Came in every morning.

163
00:24:37,127 --> 00:24:41,484
Always sat in the same place,
right there where you are now.

164
00:24:41,647 --> 00:24:44,605
A cup of chocolate and a roll.
Never coffee.

165
00:24:44,767 --> 00:24:48,726
She'd say, "If I have a coffee
I can't sleep for two days."

166
00:24:48,887 --> 00:24:52,436
- It's a question of habit.
- Would you like a chocolate?

167
00:24:52,607 --> 00:24:54,723
A question of temperament, too.

168
00:24:54,887 --> 00:24:58,926
A young girl like that killing herself.
I can't imagine why.

169
00:24:59,727 --> 00:25:05,836
No reason at all, probably. A moment
of depression and wham, it's all over.

170
00:25:08,647 --> 00:25:10,365
Robert.

171
00:25:34,847 --> 00:25:38,283
- Do you sell cigarettes?
- Yes. What would you like?

172
00:25:38,447 --> 00:25:41,917
- Gauloises bleues, please.
- I'm out of Gauloises.

173
00:25:42,087 --> 00:25:44,601
- What else?
- Gitanes and Marlboro.

174
00:25:44,767 --> 00:25:48,601
Mademoiselle Choule smoked
Marlboro. Would you like a pack?

175
00:25:48,767 --> 00:25:51,235
No. No, thank you.

176
00:26:29,007 --> 00:26:33,444
Simone Choule, the Lord
has taken thee to His bosom,

177
00:26:33,607 --> 00:26:37,441
just as the shepherd brings in
his sheep at the close of day.

178
00:26:37,607 --> 00:26:40,997
What could be more natural,
of greater consolation?

179
00:26:41,167 --> 00:26:47,242
Is it not our fondest hope that we shall
one day rejoin the flock of holy ones?

180
00:26:47,407 --> 00:26:50,638
Hope of eternal life, the true life,

181
00:26:50,807 --> 00:26:54,038
shorn of all worldly cares,

182
00:26:54,207 --> 00:26:57,961
face to face in eternal blessedness
with Almighty God,

183
00:26:58,127 --> 00:27:01,005
who through His servant,
our Lord Jesus Christ,

184
00:27:01,167 --> 00:27:03,840
died for us on the cross,

185
00:27:04,007 --> 00:27:07,556
who deigns to look down
upon us poor mortal creatures,

186
00:27:07,727 --> 00:27:10,116
full of love, infinitely merciful,

187
00:27:10,287 --> 00:27:14,565
the sick, the suffering, the dying.

188
00:27:14,727 --> 00:27:17,116
Yes, the dying.

189
00:27:17,287 --> 00:27:19,084
The icy tomb.

190
00:27:19,247 --> 00:27:22,557
Thou shalt return to the dust
from whence thou came

191
00:27:22,727 --> 00:27:24,718
and only thy bones remain.

192
00:27:24,887 --> 00:27:27,765
The worms shall consume thine eyes,

193
00:27:27,927 --> 00:27:30,361
thy lips, thy mouth.

194
00:27:30,527 --> 00:27:34,600
They shall enter into thine ears,
they shall enter into thy nostrils.

195
00:27:34,767 --> 00:27:38,077
Thy body shall putrefy
unto its innermost recesses

196
00:27:38,247 --> 00:27:40,966
and shall give off a noisome stench.

197
00:27:41,127 --> 00:27:46,042
Yea, Christ has ascended into heaven
and joined the host of angels on high.

198
00:27:46,207 --> 00:27:50,041
But not for creatures like you,
full of the basest vice,

199
00:27:50,207 --> 00:27:53,040
yearning only for carnal satisfaction.

200
00:27:54,247 --> 00:27:58,957
How dare you pester me
and mock at me to my very face?

201
00:27:59,127 --> 00:28:03,803
What audacity! What are you doing
here in my temple?

202
00:28:03,967 --> 00:28:06,356
The graveyard is where you belong.

203
00:28:06,527 --> 00:28:12,045
Thou shalt stink like some
putrefied corpse lying on the wayside.

204
00:28:12,647 --> 00:28:17,437
Verily I say unto thee, thou shalt
never enter into my kingdom.

205
00:28:24,887 --> 00:28:28,880
Four, three, two, one, zero! Our hero.

206
00:28:29,047 --> 00:28:32,642
There he is!
Hey, Trelkovsky. The lucky lodger.

207
00:28:32,807 --> 00:28:37,676
- Lucille Pampin from Nice.
- On the Riviera. Best blow job in Paris.

208
00:28:38,647 --> 00:28:41,605
- Very pleased to meet you.
- How do you do?

209
00:28:42,807 --> 00:28:45,082
What, no more chairs? What a dump!

210
00:28:45,247 --> 00:28:47,522
There is a table, right here.

211
00:28:47,687 --> 00:28:51,043
Your fiancée can come sit on my knees.

212
00:28:51,207 --> 00:28:54,882
It's against my principles.
Give me a hand.

213
00:28:55,727 --> 00:28:57,957
Grab that end, will you?

214
00:28:58,127 --> 00:29:00,243
Careful, huh?

215
00:29:01,887 --> 00:29:05,436
- Put it right in the middle.
- That's it. Much nicer.

216
00:29:05,607 --> 00:29:10,044
There's a bed here. Let's use that.
Move that table over.

217
00:29:10,207 --> 00:29:12,163
Get the table out of there.

218
00:29:12,887 --> 00:29:15,879
- Want me to do anything?
- Thank you.

219
00:29:16,047 --> 00:29:19,960
- Let me finish that.
- Just get this salad finished.

220
00:29:20,127 --> 00:29:23,483
- Have you met Viviane?
- Hello.

221
00:29:23,647 --> 00:29:25,638
Hurry up. It weighs a ton.

222
00:29:25,807 --> 00:29:28,879
- Set her down.
- Easy does it.

223
00:29:29,487 --> 00:29:31,842
What the hell is this?

224
00:29:36,047 --> 00:29:38,436
Is that one of yours?

225
00:29:41,047 --> 00:29:44,517
Oh, no, cut it out.
He's got a heart of gold.

226
00:29:45,567 --> 00:29:49,242
- How about you?
- No, I hadn't planned. I know.

227
00:29:49,407 --> 00:29:51,398
He's got the heart of a chick.

228
00:29:51,567 --> 00:29:53,717
You'd do it for a little bread.

229
00:29:53,887 --> 00:29:58,403
I wouldn't. You could offer me
a fortune, I still wouldn't dream of it.

230
00:29:58,567 --> 00:30:02,640
You think there's anyone dumb enough
to offer you a fortune?

231
00:30:02,807 --> 00:30:05,241
She's talking about the principle, jerk.

232
00:30:05,407 --> 00:30:08,479
You know what I think
of your principles?

233
00:30:08,647 --> 00:30:12,162
- What do you think?
- It's a lot of crap.

234
00:30:12,327 --> 00:30:14,682
I tell you, I'd do it for nothing.

235
00:30:14,847 --> 00:30:17,964
- Absolutely nothing.
- It takes all kinds.

236
00:30:18,127 --> 00:30:22,120
Nobody wants me to,
but I'd pay them to let me.

237
00:30:22,287 --> 00:30:25,723
I saw one once.
