475
01:01:01,207 --> 01:01:05,439
This is the guy I told you about,
the one I met at the hospital.

476
01:01:05,607 --> 01:01:08,644
We were the last to see her alive.

477
01:01:08,807 --> 01:01:12,356
Stella told us
Simone didn't seem to know her.

478
01:01:12,527 --> 01:01:15,360
- I don't think she did.
- And you?

479
01:01:15,527 --> 01:01:19,156
- Me?
- She didn't recognise you either?

480
01:01:19,927 --> 01:01:25,638
It's hard to say. I couldn't be sure
one way or the other.

481
01:01:25,807 --> 01:01:30,835
Maybe she was trying to say something
when she screamed like that.

482
01:01:31,007 --> 01:01:35,364
Anyway, that's the impression I get
when I think back on it.

483
01:01:37,007 --> 01:01:41,000
She was looking at you
when she let out that cry.

484
01:01:42,167 --> 01:01:44,442
- You think so?
- You know...

485
01:01:44,607 --> 01:01:48,998
I still have some things of hers
at home. It's depressing.

486
01:01:49,167 --> 01:01:53,206
- What have you got of hers?
- Some books, a couple of records.

487
01:02:00,087 --> 01:02:02,396
There's one of Simone's books.

488
01:02:10,167 --> 01:02:12,556
- I haven't read it.
- Nor have I.

489
01:02:12,727 --> 01:02:15,002
I'm not interested in Egyptology.

490
01:02:15,167 --> 01:02:19,285
She left it behind one evening.
You can have it if you like.

491
01:02:19,447 --> 01:02:22,883
Oh, you're very kind.
I would love to read it.

492
01:02:27,407 --> 01:02:32,686
It's a magnificent place you've got here.
Better than where I live.

493
01:02:35,607 --> 01:02:39,680
If you don't mind me asking,
is the rent very high?

494
01:02:39,847 --> 01:02:43,157
I don't pay for it.
It belongs to my brother.

495
01:02:43,327 --> 01:02:49,641
He's gone off to Peru
for a few months, a year, travelling.

496
01:02:55,287 --> 01:02:58,040
Do you have trouble
with your neighbours?

497
01:02:58,207 --> 01:03:01,597
- What sort of trouble?
- You know...

498
01:03:01,767 --> 01:03:07,444
These days, relationships with
neighbours can get quite complicated.

499
01:03:07,607 --> 01:03:13,842
You know, little things that get
blown up out of all proportion.

500
01:03:14,007 --> 01:03:16,919
- You know what I mean?
- No.

501
01:03:17,367 --> 01:03:19,358
No, I don't.

502
01:03:19,527 --> 01:03:21,916
I mind my own business.

503
01:03:24,887 --> 01:03:27,720
So do I. It's the best way.

504
01:03:30,127 --> 01:03:32,641
If you like, I'll take you home after.

505
01:03:51,167 --> 01:03:53,920
Shall we go back to your place?

506
01:03:54,487 --> 01:03:56,603
My place?

507
01:04:01,887 --> 01:04:03,479
OK?

508
01:04:03,647 --> 01:04:05,842
Sure, fine.

509
01:04:07,407 --> 01:04:10,319
Only my place is a bit...

510
01:04:11,367 --> 01:04:15,963
It's a bit difficult.
In fact, it's impossible.

511
01:04:16,127 --> 01:04:19,324
Why? Have you got a girlfriend?

512
01:04:20,847 --> 01:04:22,997
Not exactly.

513
01:04:23,167 --> 01:04:27,922
It's just that I've been repainting
and the place is in chaos.

514
01:04:28,087 --> 01:04:29,679
Chaos.

515
01:04:29,847 --> 01:04:33,601
We could still spend
a couple of hours there.

516
01:04:33,767 --> 01:04:37,999
On top of that,
my uncle is just up from the country,

517
01:04:38,167 --> 01:04:40,317
staying a few days.

518
01:04:44,567 --> 01:04:46,523
How about your place?

519
01:04:54,927 --> 01:04:56,918
Take off your coat.

520
01:05:09,007 --> 01:05:11,077
I'll be right back.

521
01:05:33,807 --> 01:05:35,638
I'd love something to drink.

522
01:05:42,247 --> 01:05:43,839
Cheers.

523
01:05:45,207 --> 01:05:46,799
Cheers.

524
01:05:55,167 --> 01:06:00,400
Why don't you take your tie off?
You look like you're choking to death.

525
01:06:02,087 --> 01:06:05,966
I found a tooth in my apartment.
It was in a hole.

526
01:06:06,127 --> 01:06:08,038
A tooth?

527
01:06:09,567 --> 01:06:11,159
In a hole?

528
01:06:11,407 --> 01:06:12,840
Yeah.

529
01:06:13,007 --> 01:06:15,043
A hole in the wall.

530
01:06:15,607 --> 01:06:17,757
Wrapped in cotton wool.

531
01:06:17,927 --> 01:06:22,318
So? No need to pull such a long face
over a tooth.

532
01:06:23,607 --> 01:06:26,246
A bit weird though, isn't it?

533
01:06:27,847 --> 01:06:33,126
Not really. When I was young,
we did it all the time.

534
01:06:33,287 --> 01:06:37,758
Whenever one of my teeth fell out
I used to hide it.

535
01:06:38,847 --> 01:06:42,237
My mother said it would turn into a coin.

536
01:06:42,687 --> 01:06:44,200
Coin.

537
01:06:50,607 --> 01:06:52,518
Oh, God.

538
01:06:52,687 --> 01:06:55,360
- Stella, I was wondering...
- Yeah?

539
01:06:55,527 --> 01:06:57,757
A tooth...

540
01:06:59,327 --> 01:07:02,046
A tooth is a part of ourselves, isn't it?

541
01:07:02,207 --> 01:07:06,644
Like a... bit of our personality.

542
01:07:09,447 --> 01:07:12,007
I don't know what you mean.

543
01:07:13,967 --> 01:07:17,562
I remember in the newspaper,

544
01:07:17,727 --> 01:07:22,960
a man lost his arm in an accident
and wanted to have it buried.

545
01:07:23,127 --> 01:07:25,436
He wanted to do what?

546
01:07:25,607 --> 01:07:30,123
- Have it buried in the cemetery.
- He must have been nuts.

547
01:07:30,287 --> 01:07:36,203
The authorities refused. The arm
was cremated and that was that.

548
01:07:36,367 --> 01:07:39,040
Where did this happen? In France?

549
01:07:39,647 --> 01:07:44,323
I wonder if they refused
to give him the ashes

550
01:07:44,487 --> 01:07:47,047
and if so, by what right?

551
01:07:48,127 --> 01:07:51,961
Haven't you got anything
more cheerful to talk about?

552
01:08:00,327 --> 01:08:02,795
All right, that'll do.

553
01:08:06,407 --> 01:08:08,204
Don't worry.

554
01:08:18,647 --> 01:08:20,603
Tell me...

555
01:08:20,767 --> 01:08:24,157
At what precise moment...

556
01:08:25,167 --> 01:08:29,604
...does an individual
stop being who he thinks he is?

557
01:08:30,727 --> 01:08:33,958
You know, I don't like complications.

558
01:08:34,407 --> 01:08:39,117
Cut off my arm.
I say, "Me and my arm."

559
01:08:40,847 --> 01:08:45,557
You cut off my other arm.
I say, "Me and my two arms."

560
01:08:47,527 --> 01:08:50,564
You... take out...

561
01:08:50,727 --> 01:08:54,720
...take out my stomach, my kidneys,

562
01:08:54,887 --> 01:08:57,685
assuming that were possible...

563
01:08:58,487 --> 01:09:01,638
And I say, "Me and my intestines."

564
01:09:04,327 --> 01:09:06,079
Follow me?

565
01:09:09,647 --> 01:09:13,401
And now, if you cut off my head...

566
01:09:13,567 --> 01:09:19,722
...would I say, "Me and my head"
or "Me and my body"?

567
01:09:22,447 --> 01:09:26,326
What right has my head to call itself me?

568
01:09:30,207 --> 01:09:31,925
What right?

569
01:10:38,527 --> 01:10:40,085
Oh, God.

570
01:11:05,007 --> 01:11:06,884
Monsieur Trelkovsky?

571
01:11:11,767 --> 01:11:13,917
Stay. Stay, Mirza, stay.

572
01:11:16,407 --> 01:11:18,523
You were out all night, huh?

573
01:11:19,407 --> 01:11:21,716
Yes, I...

574
01:11:22,007 --> 01:11:25,124
I had to stay with my uncle.
He isn't well.

575
01:11:26,247 --> 01:11:29,159
I'll tell Madame Dioz you're back.

576
01:11:29,327 --> 01:11:32,717
Madame Dioz? Who's Madame Dioz?

577
01:11:34,567 --> 01:11:36,637
This isn't for me.

578
01:11:37,327 --> 01:11:38,806
Look.

579
01:11:52,687 --> 01:11:55,599
"Best wishes from the Louvre.

580
01:11:56,247 --> 01:11:58,238
"Georges Badar."

581
01:13:09,167 --> 01:13:12,159
I'd like to have a word
with you, monsieur.

582
01:13:12,327 --> 01:13:14,477
Please come in, madame.

583
01:13:16,087 --> 01:13:18,396
I am Madame Dioz.

584
01:13:21,247 --> 01:13:26,844
- I'm very pleased to meet you.
- This is why I'm here. Please read it.

585
01:13:27,007 --> 01:13:31,558
It is a petition against
the unspeakable Madame Gaderian.

586
01:13:31,727 --> 01:13:36,676
She's gone too far this time,
and we've got to do something about it.

587
01:13:36,847 --> 01:13:40,886
Look. Even Monsieur Zy
has signed. There.

588
01:13:41,047 --> 01:13:44,244
Who is Madame Gaderian?
I don't know her.

589
01:13:44,407 --> 01:13:48,798
You don't know her? Who do you think
makes all that dreadful noise?

590
01:13:48,967 --> 01:13:51,197
It is her, my dear young man.

591
01:13:51,367 --> 01:13:55,724
She does her washing up
in the middle of the night

592
01:13:55,887 --> 01:13:59,197
and she whistles at the same time.

593
01:13:59,367 --> 01:14:03,838
- Does a civilised person do that?
- I suppose not.

594
01:14:04,007 --> 01:14:07,716
Go on, then. Sign.
It's simply a question of solidarity.

595
01:14:07,887 --> 01:14:12,836
She's making life impossible
for... for the other tenants.

596
01:14:13,007 --> 01:14:17,478
Is she the one who lives
with a disabled daughter?

597
01:14:17,647 --> 01:14:19,797
Disabled? No.

598
01:14:19,967 --> 01:14:23,084
She has a boy, a horrible, noisy brat

599
01:14:23,247 --> 01:14:27,718
who's always playing skittles
or God knows what in the corridor.

600
01:14:27,887 --> 01:14:33,519
Are you sure? Are you absolutely
certain she doesn't have a daughter?

601
01:14:33,687 --> 01:14:37,760
I don't know what goes on in their lair.

602
01:14:37,927 --> 01:14:40,282
Ask the concierge.

603
01:14:43,887 --> 01:14:47,197
I'm sorry, I'm not signing any petition.

604
01:14:48,327 --> 01:14:50,887
This woman has never bothered me.

605
01:14:51,047 --> 01:14:54,278
I've never seen her
or even heard of her.

606
01:14:54,767 --> 01:14:57,964
What apartment does she live in?

607
01:14:58,127 --> 01:15:01,119
I shall make a note of your attitude.

608
01:15:01,287 --> 01:15:06,680
I see what this is. Everyone for
himself and never mind anyone else.

609
01:15:06,847 --> 01:15:10,396
- Not at all.
- I know your type exactly,

610
01:15:10,567 --> 01:15:15,004
like that man opposite, up until
he was struck down with paralysis.

611
01:15:15,167 --> 01:15:18,477
Then his neighbours let him
stew in his own juice.

612
01:15:18,647 --> 01:15:23,118
By all means,
do whatever you think best.

613
01:15:23,287 --> 01:15:28,520
But I warn you,
don't come whining to me later.

614
01:15:35,167 --> 01:15:36,839
Bastards.

615
01:15:44,647 --> 01:15:47,605
What do you want me to do?
Drop dead?

616
01:15:51,927 --> 01:15:54,521
My wife is always...

617
01:16:05,007 --> 01:16:06,998
It's for me.

618
01:16:59,767 --> 01:17:01,723
It's no use playing innocent.

619
01:17:01,887 --> 01:17:05,880
I've heard a good deal about you,
Monsieur Trelkovsky.

620
01:17:06,047 --> 01:17:09,596
You specialise in
breaches of the peace at night.

621
01:17:09,767 --> 01:17:12,201
I'm quite amazed, Inspector.

622
01:17:13,087 --> 01:17:15,681
No one has said anything to me.

623
01:17:17,807 --> 01:17:22,927
I'm not in the habit of making noise.
I have few friends and never entertain.

624
01:17:23,087 --> 01:17:27,365
I'm not interested in your stories.
I have other things to do.

625
01:17:27,527 --> 01:17:32,476
I keep receiving complaints and
it's my duty to maintain law and order.

626
01:17:32,647 --> 01:17:38,119
So I say it once and for all,
stop whatever it is you're doing at night.

627
01:17:39,247 --> 01:17:41,522
Trelkovsky. Is that a Russian name?

628
01:17:41,687 --> 01:17:43,598
Polish.

629
01:17:44,167 --> 01:17:48,240
- So you're not French?
- I'm a French citizen.

630
01:17:48,407 --> 01:17:51,126
Let me see your identity card.

631
01:18:01,927 --> 01:18:04,316
It's in a very poor state.

632
01:18:05,527 --> 01:18:09,486
You haven't registered
your change of address.

633
01:18:09,647 --> 01:18:12,115
15 rue Sedan, where is this?

634
01:18:12,287 --> 01:18:15,723
I'm terribly sorry, I'll do it at once.

635
01:18:17,007 --> 01:18:19,441
You'll be well advised to.

636
01:18:19,607 --> 01:18:23,885
Right. This time I shall close my eyes
to the whole business.

637
01:18:24,047 --> 01:18:29,519
Make sure I don't hear about you again.
I won't have you disturbing the peace.

638
01:18:29,687 --> 01:18:31,882
Thank you very much, Inspector.

639
01:18:33,047 --> 01:18:34,560
Goodbye.

640
01:18:50,687 --> 01:18:52,518
Good afternoon, madame.

641
01:18:52,687 --> 01:18:57,238
I would like to know who registered
a complaint against me.

642
01:18:57,407 --> 01:18:59,762
Do you know who it was?

643
01:18:59,927 --> 01:19:04,318
If you didn't make so much noise
there wouldn't be any complaints.

644
01:19:04,487 --> 01:19:06,762
Was there a petition?

645
01:19:08,727 --> 01:19:14,040
Was it that woman that came to see
me the other day? Madame Dioz?

646
01:19:14,407 --> 01:19:17,524
You only have yourself to blame.

647
01:19:18,007 --> 01:19:19,998
Did you sign it?

648
01:19:53,367 --> 01:19:55,676
That's it. She's won.

649
01:19:55,847 --> 01:19:59,522
They've all signed it.
All except you, monsieur.

650
01:19:59,687 --> 01:20:02,247
Thank you. You're a good person.

651
01:20:02,847 --> 01:20:04,838
I don't like to get involved.

652
01:20:05,007 --> 01:20:09,125
Nonsense. You're a good person.
I can see it in your eyes.

653
01:20:10,807 --> 01:20:16,165
I got even with them. The concierge, too.
She's as bad as all of them.

654
01:20:16,327 --> 01:20:18,477
I paid them back, all right.

655
01:20:18,647 --> 01:20:22,196
They gave me the idea.
Do you know what I did?

656
01:20:22,367 --> 01:20:27,282
I did it. On the staircase,
in front of everyone's door.

657
01:20:30,007 --> 01:20:33,682
It's their own fault.
They gave me the idea.

658
01:20:33,847 --> 01:20:38,841
I didn't do it by your door.
I don't want to cause you any trouble.

659
01:20:39,007 --> 01:20:41,919
- How long ago?
- Just now.

660
01:20:42,647 --> 01:20:46,640
I would love to see their faces
when they find out.

661
01:20:47,527 --> 01:20:51,884
- It serves them right, all of them.
- They'll say I did it.

662
01:20:52,047 --> 01:20:54,515
Goodnight, monsieur. Sleep well.

663
01:26:08,607 --> 01:26:10,165
Hey, look.

664
01:27:12,527 --> 01:27:14,802
They'll drive me to suicide.

665
01:27:21,807 --> 01:27:24,958
All right. I'll show them.

666
01:28:34,367 --> 01:28:36,597
Gorgeous shoes, my dear.

667
01:28:38,007 --> 01:28:41,966
So pretty. Where in the world
did you find them?

668
01:28:42,127 --> 01:28:44,243
Oh, it was... I don't know...

669
01:28:49,607 --> 01:28:51,996
80 francs, you're kidding.

670
01:28:52,167 --> 01:28:54,442
Supermarket, yes.

671
01:29:00,407 --> 01:29:03,365
She's not as young as she thinks she is.

672
01:29:07,847 --> 01:29:10,520
Beautiful, beautiful.

673
01:29:10,687 --> 01:29:12,166
Adorable.

674
01:29:14,287 --> 01:29:16,642
A goddess, divine.

675
01:29:17,247 --> 01:29:18,999
Divine.

676
01:29:31,967 --> 01:29:33,764
I think I'm pregnant.

677
01:31:06,887 --> 01:31:08,400
Monsters!

678
01:31:10,407 --> 01:31:12,159
Monsters!

679
01:31:12,327 --> 01:31:17,242
They'll never turn me
into Simone Choule. Never!

680
01:31:19,247 --> 01:31:20,999
Monsieur Trelkovsky.

681
01:31:23,647 --> 01:31:27,401
Do you remember the conditions
on which I let you move in?

682
01:31:27,567 --> 01:31:31,116
I do, Monsieur Zy.
May I know what you're referring to?

683
01:31:31,287 --> 01:31:34,757
- I'm referring to women.
- Oh, yes, of course.

684
01:31:35,127 --> 01:31:38,039
Then, why do you bring them here?

685
01:31:39,127 --> 01:31:42,517
What? I never brought any women here.

686
01:31:42,687 --> 01:31:48,478
I know you did. You had a woman
in your room. You can't deny it.

687
01:31:48,647 --> 01:31:51,286
I'll turn a blind eye to it this time.

688
01:31:51,447 --> 01:31:55,406
But this is the last time.
I hope that's clear.

689
01:32:03,767 --> 01:32:06,486
Good morning, Monsieur Trelkovsky.

690
01:32:18,087 --> 01:32:20,078
Bring me a coffee.

691
01:32:20,247 --> 01:32:23,125
- You don't want a chocolate?
- No, I want a coffee.

692
01:32:23,287 --> 01:32:27,360
- You always have a chocolate.
- You never ask me what I want.

693
01:32:27,527 --> 01:32:30,360
Today I'm telling you, I'd like a coffee.

694
01:32:39,847 --> 01:32:41,599
I'm sorry, but...

695
01:32:41,767 --> 01:32:44,076
The problem is, you see...

696
01:32:44,247 --> 01:32:46,715
The machine's broken down.

697
01:32:47,207 --> 01:32:50,483
- You won't have a chocolate?
- No! Why should I?

698
01:32:50,647 --> 01:32:53,036
Nothing to get sore about.

699
01:32:53,207 --> 01:32:55,926
I'll have... a glass of red wine.

700
01:32:56,087 --> 01:32:58,555
I suppose you're out of Gauloises.

701
01:32:58,727 --> 01:33:02,879
- That's right. We've only got Marlboros.
- You can keep them.

702
01:33:04,167 --> 01:33:06,283
I know just what you're up to.

703
01:33:06,447 --> 01:33:09,007
A gang of murderers!

704
01:33:10,767 --> 01:33:13,440
No good looking at me like that.

705
01:33:13,607 --> 01:33:16,883
I know exactly what
your little scheme is.

706
01:33:34,207 --> 01:33:37,005
- What's the matter?
- My boat.

707
01:33:37,167 --> 01:33:40,477
- Which one?
- The red one.

708
01:33:42,567 --> 01:33:46,242
Now, don't cry. What's your name?

709
01:33:46,407 --> 01:33:48,079
Patrick.

710
01:33:53,327 --> 01:33:56,558
And you've lost your boat, the red one?

711
01:33:57,447 --> 01:34:00,280
OK, I'll get it back for you.

712
01:34:09,407 --> 01:34:11,363
Filthy little brat.

713
01:35:34,247 --> 01:35:36,363
It's him! He's there!

714
01:36:21,727 --> 01:36:24,685
God! What's that?

715
01:36:24,847 --> 01:36:26,485
I'll fight.

716
01:36:28,487 --> 01:36:30,603
I'll fight to the bitter end.

717
01:39:29,527 --> 01:39:31,245
<i>Who is it?</i>

718
01:39:31,847 --> 01:39:34,156
It's me, Trelkovsky.

719
01:39:39,527 --> 01:39:41,643
Were you sleeping?

720
01:39:42,247 --> 01:39:44,283
What's the matter?

721
01:39:46,367 --> 01:39:49,518
Sorry to bother you
at this hour of the morning.

722
01:39:49,687 --> 01:39:53,600
Would you mind if I stayed here
for a while?

723
01:39:57,487 --> 01:39:59,443
You're strange.

724
01:40:00,847 --> 01:40:04,886
You must tell me, then.
I wouldn't mind, really.

725
01:40:06,967 --> 01:40:09,606
No, of course you can stay.

726
01:40:17,847 --> 01:40:19,485
Look, you're hurt.

727
01:40:19,647 --> 01:40:21,877
It's nothing, really.

728
01:40:25,207 --> 01:40:28,597
- But it's filthy.
- That's nothing.

729
01:40:28,767 --> 01:40:34,046
Wait. I think I've got some...
some things here.

730
01:40:51,607 --> 01:40:53,757
How did you do that?

731
01:40:53,927 --> 01:40:55,599
It's them.

732
01:40:56,367 --> 01:40:57,880
Who?

733
01:40:58,807 --> 01:41:01,275
They're trying to kill me.

734
01:41:03,847 --> 01:41:06,315
They'll drive me to suicide.

735
01:41:06,487 --> 01:41:11,003
What are you talking about?
Who's trying to kill you?

736
01:41:11,167 --> 01:41:13,965
Stella, I've been lying to you.

737
01:41:15,927 --> 01:41:18,441
I'm living in her apartment.

738
01:41:18,607 --> 01:41:20,723
Whose apartment?

739
01:41:20,887 --> 01:41:22,764
Simone's.

740
01:41:22,927 --> 01:41:26,283
I've rented Simone Choule's apartment.

741
01:41:27,447 --> 01:41:31,520
- How did you rent it?
- She's dead because of the neighbours.

742
01:41:32,327 --> 01:41:34,636
It was a plot.

743
01:41:34,807 --> 01:41:39,881
- Plot against Simone? You're insane.
- I'm not insane. Listen.

744
01:41:40,047 --> 01:41:42,720
They forced her to commit suicide.

745
01:41:42,887 --> 01:41:45,196
I can prove it.

746
01:41:45,567 --> 01:41:49,606
And they're trying to do
the same thing to me.

747
01:41:49,767 --> 01:41:53,476
Everything's ready.
They worked it all out, every detail.

748
01:41:53,647 --> 01:41:57,322
Do you know what
they've been doing to me?

749
01:41:59,047 --> 01:42:05,680
It's so appalling,
so incredible that I can hardly tell you.

750
01:42:05,847 --> 01:42:08,315
It's true, I swear it.

751
01:42:08,487 --> 01:42:11,445
Tell me. Tell me, I'm listening.

752
01:42:15,047 --> 01:42:19,882
They've been trying to turn me
into Simone Choule.

753
01:42:22,087 --> 01:42:24,362
There now. I'm your friend.

754
01:42:24,527 --> 01:42:28,122
- They're trying...
- I'll help you. Come now.

755
01:42:28,287 --> 01:42:31,199
- To turn me...
- You're exhausted.

756
01:42:31,367 --> 01:42:33,597
...into Simone Choule.

757
01:42:36,687 --> 01:42:40,760
I'll leave Paris in a couple of days.
They'll never find me.

758
01:42:40,927 --> 01:42:44,522
You're right, yes.
That's the best thing to do.

759
01:42:45,847 --> 01:42:48,202
You're the only one I can trust.

760
01:43:25,967 --> 01:43:28,322
It's me, Stella.

761
01:43:29,167 --> 01:43:31,237
Don't be frightened.

762
01:43:32,327 --> 01:43:35,319
You do recognise me, don't you?

763
01:43:38,527 --> 01:43:40,040
Sorry.

764
01:43:40,967 --> 01:43:42,958
I was having a nightmare.

765
01:43:43,127 --> 01:43:47,598
I must get to work now. I'm late.
I'll be back around eight.

766
01:43:47,767 --> 01:43:50,076
I left your breakfast ready.

767
01:43:50,727 --> 01:43:54,402
- I love you.
- And I love you.

768
01:43:56,887 --> 01:44:00,436
I even went out
and bought you some croissants.

769
01:44:01,767 --> 01:44:04,076
Please stay. Don't leave me alone.

770
01:44:04,247 --> 01:44:08,798
I'm late. If you want to go out,
just leave the keys under the mat.

771
01:44:08,967 --> 01:44:13,597
I'll have another pair made tomorrow.
We'll each have our own set then.

772
01:44:15,087 --> 01:44:18,477
- Please don't go.
- Don't be naughty now.

773
01:44:18,647 --> 01:44:22,117
You're to be good and stay here.

774
01:44:23,367 --> 01:44:29,124
There's everything you need. If you like,
you can go out and get some fresh air.

775
01:44:29,287 --> 01:44:32,723
I'll bring food back and we'll eat in

776
01:44:32,887 --> 01:44:38,007
or go out to a restaurant if you like.
We'll see how you feel.

777
01:44:39,367 --> 01:44:41,437
See you tonight, then.

778
01:45:42,167 --> 01:45:44,317
<i>Is anyone there?</i>

779
01:45:45,847 --> 01:45:47,803
<i>Is anyone there?</i>

780
01:46:13,807 --> 01:46:15,843
Filthy bitch.

781
01:46:17,327 --> 01:46:19,522
They're all in it together.

782
01:46:20,927 --> 01:46:23,316
They're all in it together!

783
01:46:27,607 --> 01:46:29,359
They're all in it...

784
01:46:36,207 --> 01:46:38,437
They're all in it together!

785
01:47:01,127 --> 01:47:03,880
- Stop here. Stop.
- Hey, what's wrong?

786
01:47:04,047 --> 01:47:06,561
Nothing. I'm getting out.

787
01:48:00,567 --> 01:48:03,206
- Is that all right?
- Yeah.

788
01:48:55,727 --> 01:48:58,799
Thank you, monsieur.
Thank you very much.

789
01:49:08,047 --> 01:49:13,679
Have you got any idea where I can
buy a gun? I'll pay good money.

790
01:49:13,847 --> 01:49:16,202
Get out of here, you little punk.

791
01:49:16,367 --> 01:49:20,565
- He wants to buy a gun, this bugger.
- What?

792
01:49:23,007 --> 01:49:25,521
I'll tell the cops, you little shit.

793
01:49:52,807 --> 01:49:56,641
I told you not to drive so fast.
Now look what's happened.

794
01:50:09,247 --> 01:50:11,283
Monsieur, are you hurt?

795
01:50:11,447 --> 01:50:14,519
People who can't drive should take taxis.

796
01:50:14,687 --> 01:50:18,077
How dare you? My wife hasn't had
an accident in 25 years.

797
01:50:18,247 --> 01:50:22,684
He's right. The guy walked right under
the wheels. I saw it all.

798
01:50:22,847 --> 01:50:26,886
Let me through, please.
Excuse me. Let me through.

799
01:50:27,047 --> 01:50:29,356
Excuse me, I'm a doctor.

800
01:50:50,487 --> 01:50:53,604
Murderers! Murderers!

801
01:50:53,767 --> 01:50:57,999
Believe me, my wife and I are
very upset about what's happened.

802
01:50:58,167 --> 01:51:00,397
Stand back. On the kerb.

803
01:51:00,567 --> 01:51:05,960
- Officer, this is how it happened...
- Your ID, please. Yours too, monsieur.

804
01:51:06,127 --> 01:51:08,641
You're very lucky.

805
01:51:08,807 --> 01:51:11,196
Only a few scratches.

806
01:51:11,367 --> 01:51:15,724
Nothing broken.
But you should have an X-ray.

807
01:51:20,607 --> 01:51:24,441
It's nothing serious.
It's a mild case of delirium tremens.

808
01:51:24,607 --> 01:51:28,839
These people have made a statement
and offered to drive him home.

809
01:51:29,007 --> 01:51:31,123
Or should I call an ambulance?

810
01:51:31,287 --> 01:51:34,006
If the gentleman can manage, it's fine.

811
01:51:34,167 --> 01:51:38,160
We'll be glad to give this poor man
a lift home, of course.

812
01:51:43,927 --> 01:51:46,395
We'll take you home, huh?

813
01:51:54,887 --> 01:51:57,526
That is preposterous. No, please!

814
01:51:57,687 --> 01:52:02,761
They were trying to kill me. They were
playing football with a human head.

815
01:52:02,927 --> 01:52:05,202
I'll give him a shot to calm him down.

816
01:52:06,527 --> 01:52:10,202
No injection. I don't want an injection.
I don't want...

817
01:52:12,327 --> 01:52:15,763
They tried... They tried to kill me.

818
01:53:16,327 --> 01:53:18,283
Mirza, quiet down.

819
01:53:21,967 --> 01:53:26,722
Good evening, madame. This
gentleman has had a slight accident.

820
01:53:26,887 --> 01:53:30,675
- Nothing serious.
- What did he do now?

821
01:53:30,847 --> 01:53:33,805
We'd better get him up to his apartment.

822
01:53:34,847 --> 01:53:36,485
How did it happen?

823
01:53:36,647 --> 01:53:40,481
He sort of jumped out
in front of the car.

824
01:53:40,647 --> 01:53:43,957
Luckily my wife
has very good reflexes.

825
01:53:45,967 --> 01:53:48,276
What's going on here?

826
01:53:49,087 --> 01:53:50,520
It's him again.

827
01:53:52,847 --> 01:53:54,963
Oh, you bastard!

828
01:56:05,807 --> 01:56:08,275
Stay. Stay, Mirza, stay.

829
01:56:23,487 --> 01:56:26,399
- What's that?
- Down in the courtyard.

830
01:56:50,847 --> 01:56:54,396
We'd better call an ambulance.
Go get one, quick.

831
01:56:55,687 --> 01:56:57,643
You shouldn't move.

832
01:57:01,687 --> 01:57:04,042
I swear I'm not Simone Choule.

833
01:57:04,207 --> 01:57:05,720
Quick, get him a blanket.

834
01:57:05,887 --> 01:57:09,800
- Murderer!
- Another suicide! It's unbelievable.

835
01:57:09,967 --> 01:57:13,846
Look how he's dressed.
He must be insane.

836
01:57:14,007 --> 01:57:17,317
And we just finished
repairing the roof.

837
01:57:17,487 --> 01:57:21,958
I knew there was something wrong
with him the first time I saw him.

838
01:57:25,967 --> 01:57:30,836
Oh, God, Monsieur Trelkovsky.
Be reasonable, wait for the ambulance.

839
01:57:48,087 --> 01:57:50,078
You gang of killers!

840
01:57:51,367 --> 01:57:53,676
I'll show you some blood.

841
01:57:56,367 --> 01:57:58,801
You wanted a clean death, didn't you?

842
01:57:58,967 --> 01:58:02,880
- Be reasonable.
- It's going to be dirty.

843
01:58:03,047 --> 01:58:04,958
Unforgettable.

844
01:58:05,127 --> 01:58:10,838
It was better last time, wasn't it?
Well, I'm not Simone Choule.

845
01:58:11,447 --> 01:58:13,324
I'm Trelkovsky.

846
01:58:14,967 --> 01:58:16,559
Trelkovsky.

847
01:58:24,127 --> 01:58:29,155
- All right, all right. What's goin' on?
- A tenant jumped out of the window.

848
01:58:29,327 --> 01:58:33,115
- Again? You're getting them wholesale.
- Where is he now?

849
01:58:33,287 --> 01:58:38,315
He's gone back up to his apartment.
I think he had some kind of a brainstorm.

850
01:58:38,487 --> 01:58:42,241
- He's gonna jump again!
- He's not gonna do it again?

851
01:58:42,407 --> 01:58:46,400
Take it easy. Don't move.
We'll come up and get you.

852
01:58:46,567 --> 01:58:48,762
Be reasonable now.

853
01:58:52,007 --> 01:58:53,565
Oh, God, no.

854
01:58:53,727 --> 01:58:57,481
Monsieur Trelkovsky,
don't do anything silly!

855
01:59:13,007 --> 01:59:15,237
Are you a friend of hers?

856
01:59:16,167 --> 01:59:17,725
I'm sorry.

857
01:59:20,447 --> 01:59:25,601
What on earth could have happened?
Why would she do a thing like that?

858
01:59:27,567 --> 01:59:31,480
To tell you the truth,
I'm not a friend of hers at all.

859
01:59:31,647 --> 01:59:34,320
I hardly know her, actually, but...

860
01:59:36,807 --> 01:59:38,604
Simone...

861
01:59:39,927 --> 01:59:41,599
Simone...

862
01:59:42,167 --> 01:59:44,840
You do recognise me, don't you?

863
01:59:45,367 --> 01:59:48,279
It's me. Stella.

864
01:59:49,087 --> 01:59:51,726
Your friend Stella.

865
01:59:51,887 --> 01:59:53,764
Don't you recognise me?

866
02:00:02,247 --> 02:00:04,238
ENGLISH

